{"word":"ἀγαίομαι","slug":"ἀγαίομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγαίομαι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄγαμαι'><el>ἄγαμαι</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>epic and ionic for <a href='S:ἄγαμαι'><el>ἄγαμαι</el></a>, only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and in bad sense (<a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>ἄγη</el> II).\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <i>to be indignant at</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to be indignant with</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}